######################################################################
#
# install [-P predicates] <path> [arg ...]
#
# run 'exec path' if predicates evaluate to true wich is the default.
# predicates is a comma-separated list of tags that are looked up
# in the aes/vdi-trap-chain using the XBRA-protocol.
# If a tag is found in the chain the predicate evaluates true, if not found false.
# If a tag starts with '!', and a tag is found the
# predicate evaluates false, while the '!' is not used in the lookup.
# If any predicate evaluates false install will abort.
# A tag-name must be 4 characters long.
#
# example: run nvdi if neither MiNT or NVDI are found in the
# aes/vdi-trap-chain (useful on aranym+fVDI):
#
#install -P !MiNT,!NVDI c:\auto\nvdi
